observation.contraindicationText: e.g., severe combined immunodeficiency [SCID] disease, complete DiGeorge syndrome

observation.observationTitle: T-lymphocyte [cell-mediated and humoral] - Partial defects
observation.group: Administer to persons who have partial cell-mediated or humoral T-lymphocyte defects [e.g., most patients with DiGeorge syndrome, Wiskott-Aldrich syndrome, ataxia- telangiectasia].
observation.indicationText: Do not vaccinate if the patient has partial cell-mediated or humoral T-lymphocyte defects [e.g., most patients with DiGeorge syndrome, Wiskott-Aldrich syndrome, ataxia- telangiectasia].
observation.contraindicationText: e.g., most patients with DiGeorge syndrome, Wiskott-Aldrich syndrome, ataxia- telangiectasia

observation.observationTitle: T-lymphocyte [cell-mediated and humoral] - interferon-gamma/Interleukin 12 axis deficiencies
observation.group: Administer to persons who have T-lymphocyte [cell-mediated and humoral] - interferon-gamma or interferon-alpha.
observation.indicationText: Do not vaccinate with live attenuated typhoid virus [Ty21a] if the patient has T-lymphocyte [cell-mediated and humoral] - interferon-gamma/Interleukin 12 axis deficiencies.

observation.observationTitle: T-lymphocyte [cell-mediated and humoral] - interferon-gamma or interferon-alpha
observation.group: Administer to persons who have T-lymphocyte [cell-mediated and humoral] - interferon-gamma or interferon-alpha.
observation.indicationText: Do not vaccinate if the patient has cell-mediated or humoral T-lymphocyte defects related to interferon-gamma or interferon-alpha

observation.observationTitle: Persistent complement, properdin, or factor B deficiency
observation.group: Administer to persons who have persistent complement component deficiencies, including inherited or chronic deficiencies in C3, C5-9, properdin, factor D, factor H, or who are taking eculizumab [Soliris].
observation.clarifyingText: Complement deficiency disease [disorder] (24743004);Properdin deficiency disease [disorder] (81166004);Factor B deficiency [disorder] (234605000)

observation.observationTitle: Phagocytic function - Chronic granulomatous disease
observation.group: Administer to persons who have chronic granulomatous disease.
observation.indicationText: Do not vaccinate if the patient has phagocytic function - chronic granulomatous disease.

observation.observationTitle: Phagocytic function - Leukocyte adhesion defect, and myeloperoxidase deficiency
observation.group: Administer to persons who have a phagocytic function defect [e.g. leukocyte adhesion defect and myeloperoxidase deficiency].
observation.indicationText: Do not vaccinate if the patient has a phagocytic function defect [e.g. leukocyte adhesion defect and myeloperoxidase deficiency].

observation.observationTitle: HIV/AIDS - severely immunocompromised
observation.group: Administer to persons who have HIV/AIDS and are severely immunocompromised [See the CDC general recommendations for a definition of "severely immunocompromised"].
observation.indicationText: Do not vaccinate if the patient has HIV/AIDS and is severely immunocompromised [See the CDC general recommendations for a definition of "severely immunocompromised"].
observation.contraindicationText: See CDC general recommendations for guidance on defining "severely immunocompromised"

observation.observationTitle: HIV/AIDS - not severely immunocompromised
observation.group: Administer to persons who have HIV/AIDS and are not severely immunocompromised [See the CDC general recommendations for a definition of "severely immunocompromised"].
observation.contraindicationText: See CDC general recommendations for guidance on defining "not severely immunocompromised"

observation.observationTitle: Generalized malignant neoplasm
observation.group: Administer to persons who have generalized malignant neoplasm.
observation.indicationText: Do not vaccinate if the patient has generalized malignant neoplasm.

observation.observationTitle: Transplantation
observation.group: Administer to persons who have received a transplant.
observation.indicationText: Do not vaccinate if the patient received a transplant.

observation.observationTitle: Immunosuppressive therapy
observation.group: Administer to persons who are undergoing immunosuppressive therapy. Immunosuppressive medications include those given to prevent solid organ transplant rejection, human immune mediators like interleukins and colony-stimulating factors, immune modulators like levamisol and BCG bladder-tumor therapy, and medicines like tumor necrosis factor alpha inhibitors and anti-B cell antibodies.
observation.indicationText: Do not vaccinate if the patient is undergoing immunosuppressive therapy. Immunosuppressive medications include those given to prevent solid organ transplant rejection, human immune mediators like interleukins and colony-stimulating factors, immune modulators like levamisol and BCG bladder-tumor therapy, and medicines like tumor necrosis factor alpha inhibitors and anti-B cell antibodies.
observation.contraindicationText: Immunosuppressive medications include those given to prevent solid organ transplant rejection, human immune mediators like interleukins and colony-stimulating factors, immune modulators like levamisol and BCG bladder-tumor therapy, and medicines like tumor necrosis factor alpha inhibitors and anti-B cell antibodies.

observation.observationTitle: Radiation therapy
observation.group: Administer to persons who are undergoing radiation therapy.
observation.indicationText: Do not vaccinate if the patient is undergoing radiation therapy.

observation.observationTitle: Anatomical or functional asplenia
observation.group: Administer to persons with anatomic or functional asplenia, including sickle cell disease.
observation.indicationText: Do not vaccinate if the patient has anatomical or functional asplenia.
observation.contraindicationText: e.g. Sickle cell disease and other hemoglobinopathies, congenital or acquired asplenia, splenic dysfunction, and splenectomy

observation.observationTitle: Chronic renal disease
observation.group: Administer to persons with chronic renal disease.
observation.indicationText: Do not vaccinate if the patient has chronic renal disease.

observation.observationTitle: Travel to areas at risk for Yellow Fever transmission
observation.group: Administer to persons who travel to areas at risk for Yellow Fever transmission.
observation.contraindicationText: Given that changes in the designation of endemic regions can occur, travelers and health-care providers should obtain updated information from CDC, available at http://wwwnc.cdc.gov/travel/yellowbook/2010/chapter-2/yellow-fever.aspx.

observation.observationTitle: Travel to areas in which there is a recognized risk of exposure to S. typhi
observation.group: Administer to persons who travel to areas in which there is a recognized risk of exposure to S. typhi.

observation.observationTitle: Travel to or are residents of countries in which meningococcal disease is hyperendemic or epidemic
observation.group: Administer to persons who travel to or are residents of countries in which meningococcal disease is hyperendemic or epidemic.

observation.observationTitle: Travelers who plan to spend a month or longer in endemic areas during the JE virus transmission season
observation.group: Administer to persons who plan to spend a month or longer in endemic areas during the JE virus transmission season.
observation.contraindicationText: Endemic Area and transmission season is determined by country. Refer to the yellow book for a definition of the transmission season: http://wwwnc.cdc.gov/travel/yellowbook/2014/chapter-3-infectious-diseases-related-to-travel/japanese-encephalitis

observation.observationTitle: Travel to countries with high or intermediate prevalence of chronic HBV infection
observation.group: Administered to persons who travel to countries with high or intermediate prevalence of chronic HBV infection.

observation.observationTitle: Nephrotic Syndrome
observation.group: Administer to persons with nephrotic syndrome.

observation.observationTitle: Chemotherapy
observation.indicationText: Do not vaccinate if the patient is undergoing chemotherapy, including 14 days before the start of therapy and 3 months after the completion of therapy.

observation.observationTitle: History of sexual abuse or assault
observation.group: Administer to persons who have a history of sexual abuse or assault.
observation.contraindicationText: Includes children and youth who are suspected or confirmed victims of sexual abuse or assault.
